{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"55a3565c-a656-4ab6-99fa-631d0ba82d9a","content":"Yes, both are correct and remain the standard approach in .NET MAUI (including .NET 10).\n\n**`ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"`** — Add this to your `ContentPage` to keep content within the safe area (away from the notch/Dynamic Island). You'll need the namespace:\n\n```xml\nxmlns:ios=\"clr-namespace:Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific;assembly=Microsoft.Maui.Controls\"\n```\n\nOr in C# fluent style:\n\n```csharp\nOn<iOS>().SetUseSafeArea(true);\n```\n\n**`IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"`** — This lets a specific layout (like a `Grid` holding a background image) extend *past* the safe area to fill the full screen, even when the page respects it. This is the correct way to have a full-bleed background while keeping other content safe.\n\nBoth APIs are stable and this is the recommended pattern.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4cae32d7-c210-477f-809d-819e1dc9da66","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI safe area handling on iOS, specifically about two properties:\n\n1. `ios:Page.UseSafeArea=\"True\"` - a platform-specific property for ContentPage\n2. `IgnoreSafeArea=\"True\"` - a property on Grid\n\nLet me think about what I know about .NET MAUI safe area APIs:\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the iOS safe area handling has evolved. Let me check what's current:\n\n1. **`ios:Page.UseSafeArea`** - This is the iOS platform-specific attached property from `Microsoft.Maui.Controls.PlatformConfiguration.iOSSpecific`. \n\nTo use this in XAML, I need to declare the iOS namespace and then apply the property to a ContentPage. The `IgnoreSafeArea` property on layouts like Grid lets views extend beyond the safe area boundaries, which is useful when you want full-screen content. Both are valid .NET MAUI APIs for controlling safe area behavior on iOS.","outputTokens":718},"id":"2e362368-d27f-4577-a4a3-e896b8a57c2b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:56:34.889Z","parentId":"b3dac05c-f9b2-4777-a8df-18ccf7119361"}
